Good girls go bad. Bad boys do good. The football star goes to seed and the heavy girl becomes a runway model. The unhappy find peace and the restless settle. Hope is not a "thing with feathers" but seeing how your classmates have turned out, for good and for bad. You cannot escape the past and you cannot relive it. You can, however, enjoy it. So here's to the graduating class of Byram Hills High School 1983, in whom virtually every human experience and emotion can be seen. They are a unique group of people who, even if I did not realize it at the time, I am proud to have known. Indeed I am proud to know them now for, without them, I would not be the person I am today.
